  "text": "We say that a biset A is f -positive if f (A) > 0. Some important types of biset functions are given in the following definition. Biset-Function Edge-Cover with positively intersecting supermodular f admits a polynomial time algorithm due to Frank [CITATION_1] that for directed graphs computes an f -cover of cost τ (f ) (this also can be deduced using the iterative rounding method); for undirected graphs the cost is at most 2τ (f ), by a standard bi-direction reduction. Note however that the function f k-CS that we want to cover is obtained by zeroing an intersecting supermodular function on co-void bisets, but f k-CS itself is not positively intersecting supermodular.",
